rComments: Awful professor. Tests and quizzes seemed random and she seemed to give out random marks rather than follow a specific scheme. She marked my test wrong (forgot to mark and entire section) and I had to bug her every class and office hour for TWO MONTHS for her to change it. Stay away if you can.
Her TA's mark hard, her lectures are not clear, her quizzes are random, overall a very bad teacher

Not recommended. Her classes are very dull and she constantly repeats her ideas in different words. It also does not help that she talks fast and says "um" and "k" at the beginning and end of every sentence. Unfortunately, you have to attend every lecture because she gives out pop quizzes. Your mark in the course will depend on your TA.

Claims to to teach effective business English but lacks the ability to apply it herself. Drones on endlessly on what can be accomplished in a few sentences. Classes quite unpleasant- reminiscent of elementary days and scolding teachers. Marking scheme rather questionable and unreliable. Worth switching into Saturday class to get out of hers.
